<chapter id="themes">
<title>Themes</title>
  <section>
  <title><para>Introduction</para></title>
    <para>
      GPE themes consist of two parts which need to play together. 
	  These are a GTK+ theme and a Matchbox theme.
	  <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>The matchbox theme covers window decoration, default background, menu design, desktop icons.</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>The GTK theme covers application look like stock icons, button design, sliders and other widgets.</para></listitem>
	  </itemizedlist>
	  The themes usually consist of description files which are found
	  in the <filename>/usr/share/themes</filename> directory. Some of the GTK
	  themes make use if a GTK theming engine which is installed as a shared library.
    </para>
  </section>
</chapter>
